HEADWORD: Hornsnake
<hw>Horn"snake`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A harmless snake (<spn>Farancia abacura</spn>), found in the
Southern United States. The color is bluish black above, red
below.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hornstone</ent>⟦br⟧
